=== PhL-2 MCP biology-validator live demo — 2026-04-23 ===

Runs both MCP tools via the direct-CLI mode (no MCP SDK needed)
to produce a file-on-disk artefact for reviewer inspection.

## Tool 1: validate_law — PubMed co-mention heuristic

### TOP2A + EPAS1 + 'ccRCC'

{
  "query": "(\"TOP2A\"[Title/Abstract] AND \"EPAS1\"[Title/Abstract]) AND ccRCC[Title/Abstract]",
  "total_results": 0,
  "top_results": [],
  "note": "heuristic co-mention search; does not replace wet-lab validation"
}

### TOP2A + EPAS1 + 'renal'

{
  "query": "(\"TOP2A\"[Title/Abstract] AND \"EPAS1\"[Title/Abstract]) AND renal[Title/Abstract]",
  "total_results": 0,
  "top_results": [],
  "note": "heuristic co-mention search; does not replace wet-lab validation"
}

### Interpretation

Zero co-mentions of TOP2A AND EPAS1 in titles+abstracts with either
'ccRCC' or 'renal'. This is an independent signal that the 2-gene law
is NOT in the literature as a paired biomarker — it is the axis the
published ccA/ccB subtype papers identify implicitly through gene-set
analysis, but no paper we found co-reports the pair as the law.
Consistent with the paper's claim: PySR rediscovered the relationship
without being seeded with it.

